attachments.title: After An Approach From Facebook, Giphy Raises $17M At An $80M Valuation
attachments.text:
Giphy has just raised $17 million in Series B funding led by Lightspeed Venture Partners, with participation from General Catalyst and previous investors such as Lerer-Hippeau, betaworks, RRE Ventures, and CAA Ventures. Jeremy Liew, from Lightspeed, took the lead on the investment, according to a report from Business Insider.  

Giphy is a search engine for gifs, put simply. The company tags gifs to certain categories or with various keywords to make finding the perfect gif that much easier. And beyond that, Giphy ensures that artists are credited for their works and offer distribution tools like a link shortener that automatically embeds a clickable gif into tweets instead of taking up characters with the gif link and the intended hyperlink.
